Friendly reminder that I was with @KamalaHarris from the beginning & haven’t endorsed anyone since. My commentary about any of these candidates or what’s being said tonight doesn’t indicate endorsement.  And I will campaign my ass off for any one of them in the fall.   #demdebate

So many of my friends literally won’t have kids because they can’t afford childcare. And can’t afford their own student loans so can’t even fathom the idea of paying for their future kids to go to college.   This is a defining problem of our generation.   #demdebate

Thanks @amyklobuchar for reminding us that the biggest reason we can’t get drug pricing reforms done is because there are two pharma lobbyists for every one Member of Congress.  That’s why whoever the nominee is should make passing #HR1 their first priority.   #demdebate

Any single one of the health care proposals from these candidates will be so much better than what we have today. And don’t forget how much worse it could still get if Trump stays in office.   #demdebate

PLEASE NO NOT ANOTHER QUESTION ABOUT THE COST OF MEDICARE FOR ALL  Their answers aren’t going to change from the 8 million other times they’ve been asked and we are SO tired of hearing about it.   #demdebate

@ENBrown And it’s not a cop out. How many times can someone say “I’m sorry I was wrong I wouldn’t have done it if I could do it again” before we say “ok how did you learn from that and what will you do in the future?”

@ENBrown I was a teenager & led a protest to the war at my conservative HS. But I also wasn’t casting a vote given top secret briefings w/ false info & responsible for the safety of all Americans. I’m glad I wasn’t in that position but I have a small sense of what it was like to be.

Let me continue with the controversy:  You might not like that there isn’t a “plan for that” to get every troop out tomorrow or next year but it’s not that simple and if we were to immediately pull out it would be a disaster.   #demdebate

Controversial POV: when asked why you’re the best suited to be commander in chief the answer should not be “because I oppose all wars.”   When most Senators voted for a war nearly 2 decades ago bc they were deceived by Bush is not something we should still litigate.   #demdebate
